head.title: Stevie Nicks Cancels 2021 Festival Dates, Citing Rising COVID-19 Cases | Pitchfork

head.jsonld.articleBody:
[Stevie Nicks](https://pitchfork.com/artists/23583-stevie-nicks/) has canceled her headlining 2021 festival appearances at Austin City Limits, Jazz Aspen Festival, and BottleRock Napa Valley. In a statement today, she cited the ongoing nature of [the COVID-19 pandemic](https://pitchfork.com/topics/coronavirus/) as her reason for pulling out of shows.

> These are challenging times with challenging decisions that have to be made. I want everyone to be safe and healthy, and the rising COVID cases should be of concern to all of us. While I’m vaccinated, at my age, I am still being extremely cautious and for that reason have decided to skip the five performances I had planned for 2021. Because singing and performing have been my whole life, my primary goal is to keep healthy so I can continue singing for the next decade or longer. I’m devastated and I know the fans are disappointed, but we will look toward a brighter 2022.

Nicks was also set to perform at this year’s New Orleans Jazz & Heritage Festival, which was [postponed to 2022](https://pitchfork.com/news/2021-new-orleans-jazz-and-heritage-fest-canceled-due-to-covid-19-concerns/) over the weekend.

Revisit “[Stevie Nicks: Her Art and Life in 33 Songs](https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/stevie-nicks-in-33-songs/)”



[#instagram: https://www.instagram.com/p/CSaH8KNLaLI]
